<paragraph id="8BA83A22EB6AFFD9FF24E959FC92FC3B" blockId="20.[151,1437,836,1259]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6AFFD9FF24E959FE28FC1F" bold="true" box="[199,452,872,899]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Original description:</emphasis>
“shell smaller and less lofty; ovoid aperture; yellowish color”—with respect to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6AFFD9FAB5E958FE55FC3B" authority="(Muller, 1774)" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1774" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Galba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hygrophila" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="truncatula">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6AFFD9FAB5E958FEE0FC3B" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Galba truncatula</emphasis>
(Müller, 1774)
</taxonomicName>
, reported as 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6AFFD9FDA4E9BFFC92FC3B" authority="Muller." authorityName="Muller." authorityYear="1791" box="[583,894,909,935]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Limnaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionida" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="truncatula">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6AFFD9FDA4E9BFFCC9FC3B" box="[583,805,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Limnaea truncatula</emphasis>
Müller.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30D69A9EB6AFFD9FF24E980FD3AFB77" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA83A22EB6AFFD9FF24E980FD3AFB77" blockId="20.[151,1437,836,1259]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6AFFD9FF24E980FED1FC57" bold="true" box="[199,317,945,971]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Remarks:</emphasis>
having been instituted as a geographic race, we rank it subspecific, and thus available (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6AFFD9FAF1E980FA74FC57" author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1298,1432,945,971]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 10, glossary). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6AFFD9FE8AE9E4FDDAFC73" author="Hubendick, B." box="[361,566,980,1007]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="1 - 223" refId="ref17396" refString="Hubendick, B. (1951) Recent Lymnaeidae. Their variation, morphology, taxonomy, nomenclature, and distribution. Kongliga Svenska vetenskaps-akademiens Handlingar, Stockholm. Fjarde Serien, 3 (I), 1 - 223." type="journal article" year="1951">Hubendick (1951)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6AFFD9FD88E9E4FCE2FC73" author="Alzona, C." box="[619,782,981,1007]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="1 - 433" refId="ref15337" refString="Alzona, C. (1971) Malacofauna Italica. Catalogo e bibliografia dei molluschi viventi, terrestri e d'acqua dolce. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali e del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Milano, 111, 1 - 433." type="journal article" year="1971">Alzona (1971)</bibRefCitation>
listed “ 
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6AFFD9FC86E9E4FC07FC73" box="[869,1003,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">neapolitana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6AFFD9FC11E9E4FB6AFC73" author="Bellini, R." box="[1010,1158,981,1007]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="33 - 44" refId="ref15711" refString="Bellini, R. (1904 d) The freshwater shells of Naples and the neighbourhood. Journal of Conchology, 11 (2), 33 - 44." type="journal article" year="1904">Bellini, 1904</bibRefCitation>
” as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6AFFD9FAB5E9E4FE55FB8F" authority="(Muller, 1774)" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1774" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Galba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hygrophila" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="truncatula">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6AFFD9FAB5E9E4FEE0FB8F" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Galba truncatula</emphasis>
(Müller, 1774)
</taxonomicName>
, and the same holds for 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6AFFD9FD2AE9C8FC8BFB8F" author="Fasulo, G." box="[713,871,1017,1043]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref17022" refString="Fasulo, G. (2013) Molluschi extramarini (terrestri e dulciacquicoli) &quot; campani &quot; per toponimia. Notiziario S. I. M., 31 (2), 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="2013">Fasulo (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, who considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6AFFD9FBC9E9CBFE88FBAB" authority="Bellini, 1904" authorityName="Bellini" authorityYear="1904" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Limnaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionida" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="truncatula" variety="neapolitana">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6AFFD9FBC9E9CBFAE4FB8F" box="[1066,1288,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Limnaea truncatula</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6AFFD9FADCE9C8FF25FBAB" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">neapolitana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6AFFD9FF32EE2CFE88FBAB" author="Bellini, R." box="[209,356,1053,1079]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="33 - 44" refId="ref15711" refString="Bellini, R. (1904 d) The freshwater shells of Naples and the neighbourhood. Journal of Conchology, 11 (2), 33 - 44." type="journal article" year="1904">Bellini, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6AFFD9FDCCEE2CFD2BFBAB" authority="Poli, 1791" authorityName="Poli" authorityYear="1791" box="[559,711,1053,1079]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Limnaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionida" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="truncatula">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6AFFD9FDCCEE2CFD2BFBAB" box="[559,711,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">G. truncatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This taxon was never figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6AFFD9FBAEEE2CFB1FFBAB" author="Bellini, R." box="[1101,1267,1053,1079]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="33 - 44" refId="ref15711" refString="Bellini, R. (1904 d) The freshwater shells of Naples and the neighbourhood. Journal of Conchology, 11 (2), 33 - 44." type="journal article" year="1904">Bellini (1904d</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6AFFD9FAE3EE2CFAABFBAB" author="Bellini, R." box="[1280,1351,1053,1079]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="7 - 19" refId="ref15741" refString="Bellini, R. (1908 a) Etudes de Malacologie napolitaine. I. Les Mollusques terrestres et fluviatiles de la region volcanique (Vesuve et Champs Phlegrees). Annales de la Societe Royale Zoologique et Malacologique de Belgique, 42 (1), 7 - 19." type="journal article" year="1908">1908a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6AFFD9FAB0EE2DFA63FBAB" author="Bellini, R." box="[1363,1423,1052,1079]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="149 - 194" refId="ref15792" refString="Bellini, R. (1915) I molluschi extramarini dei dintorni di Napoli. Monografia sintetica. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 2, 27, 149 - 194." type="journal article" year="1915">1915</bibRefCitation>
); however, taking into account the absence of congeneric and/or similar species from the Naples area (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6AFFD9FB1DEE70FF15FBE3" author="Welter-Schultes, F." pageId="20" pageNumber="363" refId="ref19699" refString="Welter-Schultes, F. (2012) European non-marine molluscs, a guide for species identification. Planet Poster Editions, Gottingen, 680 pp." type="book" year="2012">Welter-Schultes 2012</bibRefCitation>
), as well as the fact that it is generally a very common species, we are prone to accept that it was truly described as based on 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6AFFD9FE95EEB8FDE1FB3F" authority="Poli, 1791" authorityName="Poli" authorityYear="1791" box="[374,525,1161,1187]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Limnaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionida" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="truncatula">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6AFFD9FE95EEB8FDE1FB3F" box="[374,525,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">G. truncatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This taxon was not found during samplings held in the area in the 1980’s (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6AFFD9FAB5EEB8FE74FB5B" author="Battaglini, P. &amp; Valentino, M. G." pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="233 - 259" refId="ref15554" refString="Battaglini, P. &amp; Valentino, M. G. (1981 - 1982) Aspetti ecologici di un fiume urbano ad alta alterazione ambientale (Fiume Sebeto). Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, 90 - 91, 233 - 259." type="book chapter" year="1981">
Battaglini &amp; Valentino 
<date id="FFA91CE2EB6AFFD9FE83EE9CFE74FB5B" box="[352,408,1197,1223]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" value="1981" valueMax="1982">1981</date>
</bibRefCitation>
–1982), and therefore it presumably did not survive the anthropogenic changes to which the Sebeto River has been subjected in the last century.
</paragraph>
